          class="font-kalam text-4xl"
        >
          <br />and I think Tailwind is a <span
            class="font-black text-emerald-500 font-kalam text-4xl"
            >big deal</span
          >.</span
        >
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-8 max-w-xl">
        I'm also a big fan of Astro. So I thought I'd combine the two for this
        job application.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-8 max-w-xl">
        I love designing in code, who doesnt love to dive into new projects?
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-8 max-w-xl">
        I enjoy pushing the limits to see what's acheivable using just Tailwind.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section containerClassList={["relative, overflow-hidden"]}>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black">Who is Jamie?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-4">
        I'm a product designer and front-end developer with a passion for
        creating beautiful websites and web applications.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-4">
        I have passion for CSS and saying I'm a huge Tailwind fan would be an
        understatement!
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-4">
        Based in the UK, I have been working as a product designer for the last
        two years designing dashboards, adding new features that help manage 4
        million patients with hypertension and diabetes. I'm also a registered
        pharmacist.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-4">
        I'm a self-taught designer and frontend developer. I started designing
        websites when I was 14 (I'm now 36) by creating Wordpress themes.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-4">
        I started coding around 8 years ago and fell in love with Vue, though
        I've recently picked up AstroJS and it's been great fun to work with.
        AstroJS has allowed me to dabble in SolidJS and TSX.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium mt-4">
        (I'll admit I hated TSX at first but it's growing on me).
      </p>
      <div class="">
